# Development Hour Management Tool Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and update with your actual values

# Okta OAuth2 Configuration
# Replace with your actual Okta domain (e.g., dev-123456.okta.com)
# OKTA_DOMAIN=your-domain.okta.com
# OKTA_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-from-okta-console
# OKTA_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-from-okta-console

# JIRA Base URL - Replace with your actual JIRA instance
JIRA_BASE_URL=https://your-jira-instance.atlassian.net

# JIRA Authentication - API Token only (Bearer token authentication)
# JIRA_API_TOKEN=your-api-token-here

# Optional: Database Configuration Override
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/devhour_db?createDatabaseIfNotExist=true&useSSL=false&allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=devhour_user
# SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=devhour_password

# Optional: JWT Configuration Override
# JWT_SECRET=your-production-jwt-secret-key-change-this
# JWT_EXPIRATION_MS=86400000

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Update the Okta configuration with your actual values from Okta Admin Console
# 3. Set JIRA_BASE_URL to your JIRA instance URL
# 4. Generate JIRA API token: https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens
# 5. Set JIRA_API_TOKEN with the generated token (no username required)
# 6. Restart the application

# Okta Setup Instructions:
# 1. Log in to your Okta Admin Console
# 2. Go to Applications > Create App Integration
# 3. Choose "OIDC - OpenID Connect" and "Web Application"
# 4. Configure redirect URIs: http://localhost:8080/authorization-code/callback
# 5. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret to this file
# 6. The OKTA_DOMAIN is your Okta domain (e.g., dev-123456.okta.com)